Important notes:
-----------------

1) File IO functions :
	a) High level :
	   1) Text mode - (i)Formatted (ii) Unformatted
	   2) Binary mode
	b) Low level
	
2) High level text mode formatted file IO functions : fprintf(), fscanf()

3) High level text mode, unformatted file IO functions:
   char - fgetc(), fputc()
   int, float - no functions
   string - fgets(), fputs()

4) Functions to open and close a file :
   High level - fopen(), fclose()
   Low leveel - open(), close()

5) fs = fopen(s, "r"); - Returns NULL if file is absent
                         Returns address of FILE structure, if present
   ft = fopen(t, "w"); - Creates new file if file is absent
                         Overwrites file, if present.
